\section*{Analysis 1 - Sheet 1, Exercise 1}

Prove using the definition of convergence that the sequence $(a_n)_{n \in \mathbb{N}}$ with 
$$a_n =  rac{n}{n+1}$$
converges to $1$.

	extbf{Hint:} For a given $\varepsilon > 0$, you need to find $N \in \mathbb{N}$ such that $|a_n - 1| < \varepsilon$ for all $n \geq N$.

